content.description: Start low in middle. Exit left.
Sit start on jugs below the roof. Follow the jugs out to the lip to a right hand side pull on the face. Find a way to reach a good hold on the face then top out
Sit start same as Spacial. Climb up and left all the way to the top of the Boulder and top out. Multiple ways to do the middle. Does not change the grade.
Instead of pulling the lip, make a big move straight out to a jug and use core to gain the pinchy jug just before you go up the headwall. feels about the same as rustoleum.
content.location: starts and finishes same as the rest of the routes on the rustoleum boulder

content.description: Start in the slot at the back of the cave. Work your way right to a jug rail and traverse that out to the lip. Move left and top out.
Start low. Move left then follow horizontal right out middle of the roof.https://youtu.be/CbClsJnOCU8
Start on a sloping feature with some ripples, and move up and right on sidepulls and slopers. Grab the good right hand sloper to top out.
content.location: Directly across the river from Crimpinator/Starship boulder. From the road, take the higher of the two trails and follow it along the river (river just at your left) and eventually the boulder will be on your right.

content.description: Sit start matched on a nice horizontal slot. Make a big move up to a knob or a breadloaf pinch. Once here, make a big blind move to a crimp in the seam. This move can be done several ways, depending on height, flexibility and strength.Once here, execute an iron-cross or engineer some funkyness and continue right to some buckets then topout.
A pretty little line with nice crimps and pockets. Start on a jug shelf and move up through obvious holds to top out on cool pockets.
content.location: Directly across the river from Crimpinator. About 30 feet away from Pebbles.

content.description:
Sit start in the cave with both hands on a rail. Find some feet and make a big move up to a good hold, then another big move to the lip. Once on the lip, choose from an assortment of sloping holds and continue up the face to topout.

 Landing has a few blocks on either side which could prove to be hazardous for elbows and heads.

 This climb is surprisingly good.
content.protection: 2 pads. Maybe a slider or a briefcase for the blocks.
content.location: The far right uphill side of the boulder in the dark, tight cave.

content.description: Sit start on the low shelf on the right side of the boulder. Work up into the underclings and find your way out to the crimps on the face. Top out straight up.

Sit start on a series of jugs under the roof. Climb out of the roof on large holds and a sweet blocky pinch.Once at the lip of the roof, the difficulty increases and the holds turn into slopes and crimps. Utilizing some fancy footwork, climb rightwards to some slopey crimps and figure out how to make a long reach to a better hold.Once on these better holds, continue up a few more moves on large holds with a fun press at the top.

Fun roof climbing leads to the mantle crux.

youtu.be/I7gzgWXo85M

This is a large boulder with some fantastic roof climbs. It is in a desirable, aesthetic location several yards from the creek and has a fairly flat landing.

 With a rather short approach, and a large spot to hang out, this is likely the most traveled and visited boulder in the area. It is home to many great climbs ranging from long endurance problems on big holds to some shouldery and crimpy problems as well.
